<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,267,293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,314,558]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Male and female body pigmentation including halters and legs yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1125,314,340]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1889,1915]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,292,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[228,1359,267,1833]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Adult habitus. A–B. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. E–F. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). E. ♂. F. ♀. G–H. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. (MNHN). G. ♂. H. ♀. Only dark morphs of females of species with female-limited color dimorphism are shown. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A–B); male abdominal tergites T2–T4 with a thin black stripe expanding on the middle and fainting towards the margin, T5 with a broader stripe, T6 completely black (
<figureCitation box="[708,804,386,413]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1889,1915]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,292,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[228,1359,267,1833]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Adult habitus. A–B. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. E–F. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). E. ♂. F. ♀. G–H. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. (MNHN). G. ♂. H. ♀. Only dark morphs of females of species with female-limited color dimorphism are shown. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); dorsalmost surstylus prensiseta on the same axis with remaining prensisetae, hypandrial median process weakly pointed, aedeagus finger-like (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1384,422,449]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[213,1356,343,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1400,300,1865]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. Male terminalia of the ‘D. seguyi species complex’. A. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). B. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). C. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). D–F. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. Scale bars: A–D = 50 µm; E–F = 100 µm.." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251579/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); female T2–T5 with a broad black stripe and an expanding grayish area on the margin (
<figureCitation box="[1188,1280,458,485]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1889,1915]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,292,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[228,1359,267,1833]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Adult habitus. A–B. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. E–F. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). E. ♂. F. ♀. G–H. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. (MNHN). G. ♂. H. ♀. Only dark morphs of females of species with female-limited color dimorphism are shown. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251577/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); oviscapt fourth posterior peg-like outer ovisensillum on the same axis with the third and fifth ovisensilla (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1385,494,521]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1889,1915]" captionTargetBox="[232,1361,297,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[204,1383,265,1834]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 6. Female oviscapts of the ‘D. seguyi species complex’. A–B. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). C–D. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). E–F. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). G–H. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. (MNHN). Scale bars: A, C, E, G = 100 µm; B, D, F, H = 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251581/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
), with anterior ovisensilla short and thick (
<figureCitation box="[670,762,531,558]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1889,1915]" captionTargetBox="[232,1361,297,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[204,1383,265,1834]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 6. Female oviscapts of the ‘D. seguyi species complex’. A–B. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). C–D. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). E–F. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). G–H. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. (MNHN). Scale bars: A, C, E, G = 100 µm; B, D, F, H = 50 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251581/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
