<paragraph blockId="12.[189,303,861,887]" box="[189,303,861,887]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,861,887]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,861,887]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,908,1439]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Two strains (K2 and K59) collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[688,804,908,934]" name="Kenya" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Mombasa</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[820,900,908,934]" name="Kenya" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Kenya</collectingCountry>
) in 1979 and identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[1218,1330,909,934]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis box="[1218,1330,909,934]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by T. Okada were studied in genetic studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Ohnishi S. &amp; Watanabe T. K." box="[636,946,944,970]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Science" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="801 - 807" part="1" refId="ref12740" refString="Ohnishi S. &amp; Watanabe T. K. 1984. Systematics of the Drosophila montium species subgroup: a biochemical approach. Zoological Science 1: 801 - 807." title="Systematics of the Drosophila montium species subgroup: a biochemical approach" type="journal article" year="1984">Ohnishi &amp; Watanabe 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang Z. &amp; Inomata N. &amp; Cariou M. - L. &amp; Lage J. - L. &amp; Yamazaki T." box="[956,1161,944,970]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="121 - 130" refId="ref13817" refString="Zhang Z., Inomata N., Cariou M. - L., Lage J. - L. &amp; Yamazaki T. 2003. Phylogeny and the evolution of the Amylase multigenes in the Drosophila montium species subgroup. Journal of Molecular Evolution 56: 121 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00239 - 002 - 2384 - 3" type="journal article" year="2003">
Zhang 
<emphasis box="[1037,1094,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Li Y. - F. &amp; Wen S. - Y. &amp; Kawai K. &amp; Gao J. - J. &amp; Hu Y. - G. &amp; Segawa R. &amp; Toda M. J." box="[1171,1326,944,970]" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Evolutionary Biology" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 9" part="2012" refId="ref12614" refString="Li Y. - F., Wen S. - Y., Kawai K., Gao J. - J., Hu Y. - G., Segawa R. &amp; Toda M. J. 2012. DNA barcoding and molecular phylogeny of Drosophila lini and its sibling species. International Journal of Evolutionary Biology 2012: 1 - 9. https: // doi. org / 10.1155 / 2012 / 329434" title="DNA barcoding and molecular phylogeny of Drosophila lini and its sibling species" type="journal article" year="2012">
Li 
<emphasis box="[1202,1259,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen C. - C. &amp; Watada M. &amp; Miyake H. &amp; Katoh T. K. &amp; Sun Z. &amp; Li Y. - F. &amp; Ritchie M. G. &amp; Wen S. - Y." journalOrPublisher="Zoological Science" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1056 - 1062" part="30" refId="ref12102" refString="Chen C. - C., Watada M., Miyake H., Katoh T. K., Sun Z., Li Y. - F., Ritchie M. G. &amp;. Wen S. - Y. 2013. Courtship patterns in the Drosophila montium species subgroup: repeated loss of precopulatory courtship? Zoological Science 30: 1056 - 1062. https: // doi. org / 10.2108 / zsj. 30.1056" title="Courtship patterns in the Drosophila montium species subgroup: repeated loss of precopulatory courtship?" type="journal article" year="2013">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[189,247,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
; M. Watada, pers. comm.). These strains were also sent to the laboratory of Gif-sur-Yvette in 
<collectingCountry box="[189,272,1017,1043]" name="France" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">France</collectingCountry>
, where Léonidas Tsacas and Marie-Thérèse Chassagnard worked. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T." box="[1049,1398,1016,1043]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="427 - 432" part="96" refId="ref13191" refString="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T. 1992. L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 96: 427 - 432." title="L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1992">Tsacas &amp; Chassagnard (1992)</bibRefCitation>
considered the strain of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Graber" authorityYear="1957" box="[485,618,1052,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcana">
<emphasis box="[485,618,1052,1078]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D. vulcana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R." box="[664,958,1052,1078]" journalOrPublisher="The University of Texas Publication" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 102" part="7213" refId="ref12038" refString="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R. 1972. The Drosophila melanogaster species group. The University of Texas Publication 7213: 1 - 102." title="The Drosophila melanogaster species group" type="journal article" year="1972">Bock &amp; Wheeler (1972)</bibRefCitation>
to be the true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[1145,1260,1053,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis box="[1145,1260,1053,1078]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In Tsacas’ notebook recording the strains maintained at Gif-sur-Yvette, we found a note by him considering the K59 strain to be the true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Graber" authorityYear="1957" box="[475,603,1124,1150]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcana">
<emphasis box="[475,603,1124,1150]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D. vulcana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This strain was used in the revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fallen, 1823" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1179,1312,1124,1150]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Drosophila</emphasis>
Fallén, 1823
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Da Lage J. - L. &amp; Kergoat G. J. &amp; Maczkowiak F. &amp; Silvain J. - F. &amp; Cariou M. - L. &amp; Lachaise D." box="[290,552,1160,1187]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="47 - 63" part="45" refId="ref12250" refString="Da Lage J. - L., Kergoat G. J., Maczkowiak F., Silvain J. - F., Cariou M. - L. &amp; Lachaise D. 2007. A phylogeny of Drosophilidae using the Amyrel gene: questioning the Drosophila melanogaster species group boundaries. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research 45: 47 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0469.2006.00389. x" title="A phylogeny of Drosophilidae using the Amyrel gene: questioning the Drosophila melanogaster species group boundaries" type="journal article" year="2007">
Da Lage 
<emphasis box="[401,461,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
, based on the nuclear gene 
<emphasis box="[884,968,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Amyrel</emphasis>
, although in the publication, Mount Selinda, the locality of the strain of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Graber" authorityYear="1957" box="[600,728,1196,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcana">
<emphasis box="[600,728,1196,1222]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D. vulcana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R." box="[764,1047,1196,1223]" journalOrPublisher="The University of Texas Publication" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 102" part="7213" refId="ref12038" refString="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R. 1972. The Drosophila melanogaster species group. The University of Texas Publication 7213: 1 - 102." title="The Drosophila melanogaster species group" type="journal article" year="1972">Bock &amp; Wheeler (1972)</bibRefCitation>
, was mistakenly mentioned as the source of the 
<emphasis box="[392,476,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Amyrel</emphasis>
sequence (J.-L. Da Lage, pers. comm.). In spite of the suggestion of 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T." journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="427 - 432" part="96" refId="ref13191" refString="Tsacas L. &amp; Chassagnard M. - T. 1992. L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 96: 427 - 432." title="L'identite de Drosophila (Sophophora) vulcana Graber (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1992">Tsacas &amp; Chassagnard (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, we prefer for taxonomic stability to consider both Kenyan strains to belong to the true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[243,356,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis box="[243,356,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and to preserve the concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[733,846,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis box="[733,846,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R." box="[888,1179,1305,1331]" journalOrPublisher="The University of Texas Publication" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 102" part="7213" refId="ref12038" refString="Bock I. R. &amp; Wheeler M. R. 1972. The Drosophila melanogaster species group. The University of Texas Publication 7213: 1 - 102." title="The Drosophila melanogaster species group" type="journal article" year="1972">Bock &amp; Wheeler (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. A strain collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[220,342,1341,1367]" name="Cameroon" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
by J. Pool in 2004, and preserved in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1823" box="[830,960,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Drosophila</taxonomicName>
Species Stock Center, was identified based on the mitochondrial gene 
<emphasis box="[573,919,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">cytochrome oxidase subunit 2</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[935,995,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">COII</emphasis>
) as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[1042,1152,1378,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis box="[1042,1152,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, indicating the broad distribution of this species in Africa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,1479,1686]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<bibRefCitation author="David J. R. &amp; Yassin A. &amp; Gidaszewski N. &amp; Debat V." box="[189,424,1479,1505]" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="336 - 342" part="50" refId="ref12333" refString="David J. R., Yassin A., Gidaszewski N. &amp; Debat V. 2014. Drosophilids (Diptera) from Mayotte island: an annotated list of species collected in 2013 and comments on the colonisation of Indian Ocean Islands. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France 50: 336 - 342. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2014.938548" title="Drosophilids (Diptera) from Mayotte island: an annotated list of species collected in 2013 and comments on the colonisation of Indian Ocean Islands" type="journal article" year="2014">
David 
