<bibRefCitation author="Yassin A. &amp; Delaney E. K. &amp; Reddiex A. J. &amp; Seher T. D. &amp; Bastide H. &amp; Appleton N. C. &amp; Lack J. B. &amp; David J. R. &amp; Chenoweth S. F. &amp; Pool J. E. &amp; Kopp A." box="[197,429,1587,1614]" journalOrPublisher="Current Biology" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="2412 - 2422" part="26" refId="ref13717" refString="Yassin A., Delaney E. K., Reddiex A. J., Seher T. D., Bastide H., Appleton N. C., Lack J. B., David J. R., Chenoweth S. F., Pool J. E. &amp; Kopp A. 2016. The pdm 3 locus is a hotspot for recurrent evolution of female-limited color dimorphism in Drosophila. Current Biology 26: 2412 - 2422. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cub. 2016.07.016" title="The pdm 3 locus is a hotspot for recurrent evolution of female-limited color dimorphism in Drosophila" type="journal article" year="2016">
